The paper deals with the testing of properties of Boolean-valued functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and property testing (cs.DS). The paper also discusses graph properties, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of densities and partitions suggests information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) as possible sub-categories as well.
